WE CAN'T AFFORD THIS.

31:34.340 --> 31:35.910
COME LOOK.
- [murmurlng]

31:35.960 --> 31:36.608
- SEE FOR YOURSELF.

31:36.650 --> 31:38.436
[metal crashes, toy squeaks]

31:38.480 --> 31:39.469
- SHH! THE BABY'S SLEEPING!
- I KNOW, I KNOW.

31:39.510 --> 31:41.478
OH, NO, SHE'S NOT UP.

31:41.520 --> 31:43.659
OKAY, I CAN'T LIVE
IN THIS ROOM ANYMORE.

31:43.690 --> 31:44.725
- YEAH, WE CAN'T AFFORD TO LIVE
IN THIS ROOM ANYMORE.

31:44.760 --> 31:46.796
- THAT'S HOW MUCH IT'S GONNA
COST TO STAY HERE?

31:46.830 --> 31:47.933
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

31:47.970 --> 31:50.894
- THAT'S WHAT I'M TRYING
TO SAY.

31:50.940 --> 31:52.214
- HONEY, MY CHEST
JUST CONSTRICTED.

31:52.250 --> 31:55.048
LIKE, SINCERELY,
I HAVE CONSTRICT ION IN MY CHEST.

31:55.080 --> 31:56.115
- [laughs]
- LIKE THEY SAY.

31:56.150 --> 31:57.424
- JUST BREATHE.
[Inhales]

31:57.460 --> 31:59.041
WE'RE GONNA GET THROUGH IT.
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

31:59.080 --> 32:01.219
- HOW CAN IT BE THAT MUCH?
THIS PLACE IS A DUMP!

32:01.260 --> 32:02.420
- YEP.

32:02.470 --> 32:04.153
- HOW COME YOU'RE NOT
ALL SPUN OUT ABOUT THIS?

32:04.190 --> 32:05.009
- BECAUSE, UM,
WELL, GROWING UP,

32:05.060 --> 32:08.268
WE WENT THROUGH A LOT WORSE,
SO...

32:08.300 --> 32:10.359
WE GOT THROUGH IT THEN.
WE'LL GET THROUGH IT NOW.

32:10.410 --> 32:11.195
TOGETHER. WE GOT THIS.
WE'LL--

32:11.230 --> 32:14.575
- WHY DO YOU HAVE ZERO

32:14.620 --> 32:15.951
FOR THE HOUSE RENTAL BUDGET?

32:16.000 --> 32:16.898
WE'RE--IF WE'RE LEAVING HERE,

32:16.930 --> 32:19.137
HOW ARE WE GONNA RENT A HOUSE
FOR ZERO?

32:19.170 --> 32:21.172
- I DOUBT YOUR PARENTS
WILL CHARGE US RENT MONEY.

32:21.210 --> 32:23.792
- MY PARENTS? WHAT--

32:23.830 --> 32:27.140
- YEAH.
YOU NEED TO CALL THEM.

32:27.180 --> 32:28.386
_ UH--
- YEAH, WELL--

32:28.420 --> 32:31.287
- I'M NOT--
- THAT'S WHAT WE NEED TO DO.

32:31.320 --> 32:33.459
- [sighs]

32:35.400 --> 32:38.153
OKAY, I'M GONNA CALL 'EM.
- MM-HMM.

32:38.190 --> 32:39.361
- BUT HONESTLY,
WHEN YOU SAID THAT NOW,

32:39.400 --> 32:40.810
MY ARM JUST GOT NUMB
ON THE LEI-T SIDE.

32:40.850 --> 32:41.919
- AW, LET ME MASSAGE IT FOR YOU.
- LIKE, IT'S FOR REAL.

32:41.960 --> 32:44.019
CARDIAC ARREST.
I KNOW YOU THINK THIS IS FUNNY,

32:44.060 --> 32:45.436
BUT THAT'S ONE OF THE SIGNS,
IS YOUR THING GOES NUMB.

32:45.480 --> 32:47.050
- IS IT?
- YEAH, YOUR RIGHT OR LEI-T.

32:47.100 --> 32:48.681
- IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.
- I'M NOT SURE WHICH ONE.

32:48.720 --> 32:50.096
- I'LL JUST MAKE SURE
THAT YOU'RE ALL WARMED UP.

32:50.140 --> 32:51.232
- AS LONG AS MY PHONE DIALING
HAND'S GOOD,

32:51.270 --> 32:54.273
YOU'RE FINE.
- EXACTLY, EXACTLY.

32:56.800 --> 32:59.132
[footsteps approach]

32:59.180 --> 33:02.308
- OKAY.
THAT'S THE LAST OF IT.

33:02.350 --> 33:03.419
- OKAY.

33:03.460 --> 33:05.906
- UM, I WAS GONNA COME BY
IN THE MORNING

33:05.940 --> 33:07.828
AND TAKE THE KIDS TO SCHOOL.

33:07.880 --> 33:10.849
- OKAY.

33:10.880 --> 33:14.179
- SO I GUESS
THAT'S EVERYTHING.

33:14.230 --> 33:15.811
- I'LL WALK YOU OUT.

33:15.850 --> 33:17.124
- OH, YOU DON'T--

33:17.160 --> 33:19.503
YOU DON'T HAVE TO--

33:19.540 --> 33:21.929
- [sighs]

33:21.960 --> 33:24.406
- UM...

33:24.450 --> 33:27.203
WHEN I, UH,

33:27.240 --> 33:28.821
WHEN I PICK
THE KIDS UP TOMORROW,

33:28.860 --> 33:30.339
UM, SHOULD I USE THE KEY,

33:30.380 --> 33:34.316
OR WOULD IT BE BETTER FOR YOU
IF I KNOCKED?

33:36.110 --> 33:39.170
- JUST COME IN.

33:39.220 --> 33:42.280
- YEAH, OKAY.

33:45.330 --> 33:48.083
WELL--

33:49.260 --> 33:53.048
- ALL MY TEARS
HAVE BEEN USED UP

33:53.100 --> 33:57.469
ON ANOTHER LOVE,
ANOTHER LOVE

33:57.510 --> 34:02.686
ALL MY TEARS
HAVE BEEN USED UP

34:04.730 --> 34:09.724
OH

34:10.460 --> 34:14.829
OH OH OH OH
OH OH OH

34:17.330 --> 34:22.495
OH OH OH OH OH OH OH

34:28.440 --> 34:32.194
OH OH

34:35.760 --> 34:36.715
- REMEMBER WHEN

34:36.760 --> 34:38.899
WE WERE YOUNG

34:38.930 --> 34:42.343
WE FELT LIKE
THE LUCKIEST ONES

34:42.390 --> 34:45.382
NOTHING TO WORRY 'BOUT

34:45.420 --> 34:47.900
THE WHOLE WORLD
WAS A HAND-ME-DOWN

34:50.290 --> 34:51.871
TURN IT UP, TURN IT UP

34:51.910 --> 34:55.459
TURN UP YOUR RADIO LOUD

34:55.500 --> 34:59.288
DON'T FORGET
WHERE YOU COME FROM

34:59.330 --> 35:02.265
IT'S TOO SOON TO BE PROUD

35:02.300 --> 35:04.268
REMEMBER WHEN

35:04.300 --> 35:07.645
WE WERE YOUNG

35:16.730 --> 35:17.242
- I THINK WE GOT IT.

35:17.280 --> 35:21.034
- NO, JUST ONE MORE.

35:21.080 --> 35:23.184
[click]

35:25.050 --> 35:28.770
GOING...

35:28.810 --> 35:31.392
GOING...

35:31.430 --> 35:32.909
[click]

35:32.950 --> 35:34.087
GONE.

35:34.130 --> 35:36.360
- GIMME THAT.

35:39.100 --> 35:40.818
- SO?

35:40.860 --> 35:43.476
- SO WHAT?

35:43.520 --> 35:46.580
- IT WAS A GOOD IDEA, HUH?

35:46.620 --> 35:48.349
- IT WAS A WAY To GO.
- PFFFI'.

35:48.380 --> 35:50.621
COME ON.
LOOK AT THIS.

35:50.660 --> 35:52.139
THIS IS AMAZING.

35:52.180 --> 35:53.966
THAT WAS AN AMAZING DAY.

35:54.010 --> 35:56.001
I WANT TO DO THAT
EVERY DAY.

35:56.050 --> 35:59.759
- YEAH, WELL, WE DID IT.

35:59.810 --> 36:02.358
HOW 'BOUT A DRINK NOW?
THAT'S WHAT I WANT.

36:02.400 --> 36:04.049
_ UH--
- I MEAN TO CELEBRATE,

36:04.090 --> 36:06.251
THAT'S ALL.
- OH, TO CELEBRATE?

36:06.300 --> 36:07.699
- YEAH.
- OH, NO, THEN I CAN'T.

36:07.750 --> 36:09.320
- YOU GOT SOMEWHERE TO GO?
- [laughs]

36:09.370 --> 36:11.782
WELL, I CAN'T CELEBRATE
SOMETHING THAT, UH,

36:11.820 --> 36:14.095
YOU DIDN'T SAY
WAS A THING TO CELEBRATE.

36:14.130 --> 36:17.065
IF YOU DON'T THINK
IT WAS A GOOD IDEA,

36:17.100 --> 36:18.829
THEN I CAN'T CELEBRATE...

36:18.860 --> 36:19.679
- ALL RIGHT.
- WITH YOU.

36:19.720 --> 36:23.724
- LOOK, YOU HAD A--
IT WORKED OUT.

36:23.760 --> 36:24.931
- OH, GOD, SAY IT.
- IT WORKED OUT.

36:24.970 --> 36:26.722
- I DID GOOD.

36:26.770 --> 36:28.522
- YOU DID ALL RIGHT.
- THANK YOU.

36:28.560 --> 36:29.902
- THAT ONE BY THE TACO TRUCK?
- RIGHT?

36:29.940 --> 36:31.419
- THAT KIND OF IMPRESSED ME
A LITTLE BIT.

36:31.460 --> 36:32.188
- THANK YOU VERY MUCH...
- YEAH.

36:32.220 --> 36:34.939
- FOR SAYING SO.
APPRECIATE IT.

36:34.980 --> 36:36.254
- ALL RIGHT,
CAN WE DRINK NOW?

36:36.290 --> 36:38.565
- I ACTUALLY CAN'T.

36:38.610 --> 36:39.986
- OH, THAT'S--THAT IS COLD.
- NO.

36:40.020 --> 36:42.124
- YOU MAKING ME LIE
LIKE THAT.

36:42.160 --> 36:43.388
- I'M JUST KIDDING.
I'M KIDDING.

36:43.440 --> 36:45.055
I MEAN, I HAVE A--
I HAVE A DINNER LATER,

36:45.090 --> 36:46.364
BUT I'LL HAVE A DRINK NOW,
YEAH.

36:46.410 --> 36:48.640
- THEY GOT A LITTLE
MEXICAN THING UP THE ROAD.

36:48.680 --> 36:49.749
- OOH, GOOD.

36:49.790 --> 36:50.927
- IT'S, UH,
IT'S A DIVE-Y PLACE.

36:50.960 --> 36:52.131
- THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

36:52.170 --> 36:53.580
- YOU'RE BUYING.
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?

36:53.620 --> 36:54.405
- WHAT'S THAT?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

36:54.450 --> 36:57.305
- YOU'RE THE BOSS.
THE BOSS BUYS.

36:57.350 --> 37:00.103
THAT'S, LIKE,
CALIFORNIA CODE.

37:00.140 --> 37:02.722
- [sighs]
OKAY.

37:05.250 --> 37:06.979
- STAYED UP THERE
UNTIL NORA STARTED

37:07.010 --> 37:08.489
HER SWEET LITTLE SNORE.

37:08.530 --> 37:09.804
- [chuckles]
OH.

37:09.840 --> 37:10.704
- WHAT'S UP?

37:10.740 --> 37:12.423
- UH, PRINCIPAL RADFORD CALLED.

37:12.470 --> 37:13.607
- YEAH?
- THEY'RE GONNA MOVE--YEAH.

37:13.640 --> 37:17.121
THEY'RE GONNA MOVE MAX
TO A DIFFERENT HISTORY CLASS.

37:17.160 --> 37:18.058
WHICH IS GOOD.
- THAT'S GOOD.

37:18.090 --> 37:19.057
- YEAH.

37:19.090 --> 37:20.842
- I GUESS.

37:20.890 --> 37:22.858
- DOESN'T REALLY FEEL LIKE
A VICTORY, THOUGH, DOES IT?

37:22.890 --> 37:23.925
- NO.
- IT'S SORT OF--

37:23.960 --> 37:26.372
- FEELS LIKE A BAND-AID
PLACED OVER A--

37:26.410 --> 37:27.581
WHAT DO YOU CALL
WHEN YOUR ARTERY

37:27.620 --> 37:29.372
IS JUST SPURTING BLOOD,
AND YOU--

37:29.410 --> 37:31.583
- HIGH SCHOOL.
- RIGHT.

37:31.620 --> 37:33.064
- NO, I'M SERIOUS, HONEY.
HIGH SCHOOL.

37:33.110 --> 37:34.589
I'M WORRIED.
I REALLY AM.

37:34.630 --> 37:35.654
- I'M WORRIED TOO.
- AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,

37:35.700 --> 37:36.894
HE'S NOT GOING
TO THE PUBLIC HIGH SCHOOL HERE.

37:36.940 --> 37:39.147
HE CAN'T.

37:39.180 --> 37:40.977
- [sighs]
OKAY.

37:41.010 --> 37:42.420
- YOU KNOW?

37:42.460 --> 37:44.257
- WELL, WE'LL FIGHT
THE DISTRICT

37:44.290 --> 37:44.904
AND SEE IF WE CAN GET HIM PLACED
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

37:44.950 --> 37:46.838
- WHERE?
- I DON'T KNOW.

37:46.880 --> 37:48.393
- THIS IS A LIST OF SCHOOLS
IN THE BAY AREA

37:48.430 --> 37:49.397
FOR KIDS
WITH SPECIAL NEEDS.

37:49.430 --> 37:50.704
HE DOESN'T FIT IN ANYWHERE.

37:50.750 --> 37:52.229
THERE'S NOWHERE
TO PUT HIM.

37:52.270 --> 37:53.532
- SO YOU'RE SAYING
NO PUBLIC SCHOOL?

37:53.580 --> 37:54.911
- NO.

37:54.960 --> 37:56.291
- WELL, WHAT ABOUT GATEWAY?

37:56.340 --> 37:57.614
NOEL LESSING'S DONE
GREAT THERE.

37:57.650 --> 37:59.857
- GATEWAY IS GREAT FOR KIDS
LIKE NOEL LESSING.

37:59.890 --> 38:00.549
HE HAS SEVERE AUTISM.

38:00.580 --> 38:02.468
- WELL, I--
- YOU KNOW?

38:02.520 --> 38:03.714
- WELL, WHAT ABOUT PROVIDENCE?

38:03.760 --> 38:05.409
- MAX'S TEST SCORES
ARE WAY TOO HIGH.

38:05.450 --> 38:08.271
WAY TOO HIGH.

38:08.320 --> 38:09.719
- SINCE WHEN ARE
HIGH TEST SCORES PROBLEMATIC?

38:09.770 --> 38:10.691
- I DON'T KNOW.

38:10.730 --> 38:11.583
- I'M VERY FRUSTRATED,
YOU KNOW.

38:11.630 --> 38:13.382
I HATE TO SEE MAX
GET SHUFFLED AROUND

38:13.420 --> 38:14.899
ALL THE TIME LIKE THIS.

38:14.940 --> 38:16.498
WHERE DO YOU PUT A KID
WHO DOESN'T BELONG ANYWHERE?

38:16.530 --> 38:17.838
- I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S THE SYSTEM.

38:17.880 --> 38:19.768
I MEAN, WE'RE STUCK
WITH THE SYSTEM.

38:19.810 --> 38:21.562
AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,
THE ONLY WAY

38:21.600 --> 38:24.535
TO GET A SCHOOL FOR HIM
IS IF WE START ONE OURSELVES.

38:30.920 --> 38:31.716
[keyboard clicking]

38:31.750 --> 38:33.229
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- NOTHING.

38:33.270 --> 38:34.999
I'M NOT DOING ANYTHING.
- KRISTINA, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

38:35.030 --> 38:36.201
- I'M NOT DOING ANYTHING.

38:36.240 --> 38:39.368
I JUST--JUST HOLD ON
FOR A SECOND.

38:39.420 --> 38:41.888
I MEAN, I'M JUST GONNA CHECK
SOMETHING OUT.

38:41.940 --> 38:43.999
- "HOW TO START A SCHOOL"?
- NOTHING.

38:44.040 --> 38:45.894
I'M NOT DOING THAT.

38:45.940 --> 38:46.861
YOU--
- THAT'S CRAZY.

38:46.910 --> 38:48.286
- IT'S SO INSANE.

38:48.320 --> 38:51.528
IT'S INSANE...
BUT IT ISN'T, IS IT?

38:51.570 --> 38:52.559
- I THINK THAT
THIS LOOKS LIKE A LOT

38:52.600 --> 38:55.114
OF BUREAUCRATIC RED TAPE
AND A WHOLE LOT OF WORK.

38:55.160 --> 38:57.151
- I KNOW,
BUT HOW HARD CAN IT BE?

38:57.190 --> 38:58.327
I MEAN, THINK ABOUT IT.

38:58.370 --> 39:00.679
YOU STARTED A STUDIO,

39:00.710 --> 39:02.189
A RECORDING STUDIO,
RIGHT?

39:02.230 --> 39:03.709
- YES, THAT WAS NOT EASY.
- YEAH.

39:03.750 --> 39:04.364
- AND YOU RAN FOR MAYOR...
- I DID.

39:04.410 --> 39:04.978
- WHICH WAS ALSO NOT EASY.

39:05.030 --> 39:07.123
- NOT EASY, BUT, I MEAN--

39:07.170 --> 39:08.376
- AND, I GUESS,
WHAT DO WE NEED?

39:08.410 --> 39:09.195
JUST A BUILDING
AND SOME TEACHERS.

39:09.240 --> 39:10.468
- AND MAYBE
A HOT LUNCH PROGRAM.

39:10.520 --> 39:13.819
- HOW HARD CAN THAT BE?

39:13.860 --> 39:15.066
IF ANYBODY CAN DO THIS...
- OKAY, THIS IS CRAZY.

39:15.110 --> 39:16.304
THIS IS CRAZY.
- YOU CAN DO IT.

39:16.350 --> 39:17.317
- I CAN. WE CAN.

39:17.350 --> 39:18.556
- [laughing]
HEY.

39:18.590 --> 39:20.000
THANKS FOR LET-TIEIYNG US DO THIS.

39:20.040 --> 39:21.484
- OH, YOU'RE WELCOME.

39:21.530 --> 39:23.486
THE MOLD THING'S
NOT CONTAGIOUS, IS IT?

39:23.530 --> 39:25.077
- HEY, JABBAR.
- WE MAY HAVE SOME ON OUR SHOES.

39:25.120 --> 39:26.382
WE'LL LEAVE THEM
AT THE DOOR,

39:26.430 --> 39:28.045
IF THAT MAKES YOU FEEL
MORE COMFORTABLE.

39:28.080 --> 39:29.354
- HI.
- IS SHE SLEEPING?

39:29.400 --> 39:31.391
- YEAH.
- I PROMISE

39:31.430 --> 39:32.909
WE'LL STAY OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

39:32.950 --> 39:35.532
- NO PROBLEM, I MEAN--
- NO, NO, IT'S--

39:35.580 --> 39:36.979
- IT'S A BIG HOUSE.
SOMEONE'S GOTTA FILL IT,

39:37.020 --> 39:38.499
YOU KNOW.
- DAD SAID I GET

39:38.540 --> 39:39.507
WHATEVER ROOM I WANT.

39:39.540 --> 39:40.199
- OH, YEAH?
- WHAT?

39:40.230 --> 39:42.619
- [stammers]
- I DON'T--

39:42.650 --> 39:44.709
WELL, MOM SAID YOU'LL ASK
YOUR GRANDPARENTS POLITELY

39:44.760 --> 39:46.512
WHERE THEY'D LIKE US.
WE CAN TAKE THE GUESTHOUSE

39:46.550 --> 39:47.778
IF THAT'S EASIER
FOR YOU GUYS.

39:47.830 --> 39:48.922
- WE'RE HAPPY TO DO THAT.
THERE ARE FOUR OF US.

39:48.970 --> 39:50.130
ONE OF US IS TEETHING, THOUGH.
I WILL MENTION THAT.

39:50.180 --> 39:53.035
- NO, IT'S--BE JUST GREAT
TO HAVE KIDS IN THE HOUSE AGAIN.

39:53.080 --> 39:54.240
- YEP.
- RIGHT?

39:54.280 --> 39:56.453
- YEAH.
- THEN I GET DAD'S OLD ROOM!

39:56.490 --> 39:57.070
- OKAY!
- LOOK AT THAT.

39:57.110 --> 39:59.385
- HUH?
- HE CLAIMED IT.

39:59.430 --> 40:02.354
- I WOULD'VE TAKEN
THE MASTER SUITE, JABBAR.

40:02.400 --> 40:03.947
THAT WAS ON THE TABLE, RIGHT?

40:03.980 --> 40:06.426
- THE WEEKS LEAD UP
TO LEAVING

40:06.470 --> 40:10.122
SUMMER'S GONNA GET
CRUSHED

40:10.160 --> 40:17.305
COME CLEAN
WHEN THE LINES GET BLURRY

40:17.340 --> 40:20.446
COME CLEAN
WHEN THE DOWN

40:20.480 --> 40:23.108
GETS DIRTY

40:23.140 --> 40:24.129
HOLDING YOUR BREATH

40:24.180 --> 40:26.239
- MOMMY...
- HI.

40:26.280 --> 40:27.963
- I DON'T FEEL GOOD.

40:28.010 --> 40:29.170
I HAVE A TUMMY ACHE.

40:29.210 --> 40:31.144
- OH, SWEETIE--
- I DON'T FEEL TOO GOOD EITHER.

40:31.180 --> 40:34.809
- I THINK WE BETTER
CALL DAD.

40:34.840 --> 40:36.637
- I WILL TUCK YOU BOTH
BACK IN,

40:36.670 --> 40:38.217
AND I'LL READ YOU
ANOTHER BEDTIME STORY.

40:38.260 --> 40:39.488
I BET THAT'LL HELP.

40:39.540 --> 40:42.111
- I DON'T FEEL GOOD.

40:42.160 --> 40:45.391
- GET YOUR COATS.

40:45.440 --> 40:46.577
OKAY?
- WHERE ARE WE GOING?

40:46.610 --> 40:48.191
- THIS IS GONNA BE GREAT.

40:48.230 --> 40:49.572
I PROMISE.

40:49.610 --> 40:51.305
- NOW, WHERE WAS I?
WAS I IN THE RED?

40:51.340 --> 40:52.853
- YEAH, YOU WERE ON THE RED.
- OKAY.

40:52.890 --> 40:55.859
- WHOSE TURN IS IT?
- HER TURN.

40:55.900 --> 40:57.822
- HEY.
- HI.

40:57.860 --> 40:59.066
- HEY, SWEETHEART.
LOOK WHO'S HERE.

40:59.110 --> 41:01.169
- HEY. I SHOULD HAVE
CALLED MAYBE, BUT...

41:01.210 --> 41:04.794
- HI, SWEETHEART.
HI, SWEETIE PIE.

41:04.840 --> 41:06.068
- UH, JABBAR, LET'S SHOW
YOUR COUSINS YOUR NEW ROOM.

41:06.110 --> 41:08.556
- YEAH. THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.
- I'LL TAKE THE BABY UPSTAIRS.

41:08.600 --> 41:10.181
- COME ON, GUYS,
LET'S GO.

41:10.220 --> 41:11.016
- 'SUP?
- HEY.

41:15.260 --> 41:17.364
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

41:17.400 --> 41:18.879
- OH, I JUST--

41:18.920 --> 41:21.502
I HAD TO GET
OUT OF THE HOUSE.

41:21.540 --> 41:25.089
- WHY?
WHAT'S UP?

41:25.130 --> 41:29.021
- UM...
[exhales]

41:29.070 --> 41:31.652
THERE'S SO MUCH
THAT I HAVEN'T TOLD YOU GUYS.

41:31.690 --> 41:33.555
[crying]
UM--

41:33.590 --> 41:37.765
- SWEETIE, WHAT IS IT?

41:37.800 --> 41:40.837
- MY MARRIAGE MIGHT BE OVER.

41:40.870 --> 41:41.791
THAT'S--

41:43.190 --> 41:47.524
- OH, SWEETH EART.

41:47.570 --> 41:48.423
- [crying]
JUST WANTED TO COME HOME,

41:48.470 --> 41:49.357
YOU KNOW?

41:49.400 --> 41:51.459
- SWEETIE.

41:51.500 --> 41:54.219
- AT SOME POINT
WE ALL HAVE TO

41:54.270 --> 41:57.740
COME CLEAN

41:57.790 --> 41:59.234
- OHH.
